programme.desc: When Julie and her family moved into their dream home in suburban New Jersey they quickly realized they were not alone.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Haunted Connection
programme.desc: P.R.S. is called in to help a young mother tormented by an otherworldly connection to a teenage girl murdered in her neighborhood years ago. Could she have psychic ability or is there a more sinister force at work?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Church of the Damned
programme.desc: Jason and his family can no longer do renovations of an abandoned Kansas church, especially after they found their father in the basement crying and frightened because of the menacing activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Who Is the Lurking Man?
programme.desc: PRS travels to Newcastle, CA to investigate a house with paranormal forces so strong, the family has cleared out. Ryan believes the Native American land may hold the key to the mystery and leads the team in a fight to reclaim a scared family's house.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Suicide Possession
programme.desc: Joan and her boyfriend Tony are seeing apparitions in their New Jersey home. Both are concerned that the spirits are influencing their behavior: a non-drinker, Tony has turned to the bottle while Joan has thoughts of harming herself.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Hostage to Fear
programme.desc: P.R.S. is summoned to help a family who has been haunted for years by spirits lurking in the house. Upon arrival the team finds a family that has become prisoners in their own home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Man of the House
programme.desc: PRS is called to help a grandmother and her frightened grandson when renovations on her 19th century house stir up the pipe-smoking specter of a former tenant named Alfred.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Bedroom Eyes
programme.desc: PRS travels to rural Pennsylvania to investigate a haunting that began after a new couple moved into an old family farm.?Over the next three days, hidden tragedies are uncovered and latent psychic abilities are revealed.

programme.title: Paranormal State: School House Haunting
programme.desc: PRS travels to Massachusetts to investigate an old schoolhouse where children's voices disturb a couple who've made it their home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Laws of Attraction
programme.desc: When Paula's young autistic son Michael, with limited verbal skills uttered the words "Go away scary dead boy" -- it sent a chill up her spine.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Lost Souls
programme.desc: PRS and Psychic/medium Michelle Belanger investigate a Pennsylvania home; where a mother named Kathy and her son Michael have both felt the presence of a young boy and hear voices calling, "Mom?" but no one is there.

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Firehouse
programme.desc: Everyone from the chief to the trainees at the Clementon Fire Department is convinced that the ghost of a former member is haunting their firehouse.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Dartford Library
programme.desc: Dartford Library comes under Yvette and the crew's scrutiny as they experience strange poltergeist activity involving books, and contact the denizens that appear to cling to the building.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Stockport Workhouse
programme.desc: The Stockport Workhouse opened on a bleak Christmas Day in 1841 and quickly filled with the desperate and jobless. The Dickensian atmosphere gives Yvette and the team a night to remember!

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tatton Park, Old Hall
programme.desc: Journalist Carol Thatcher joins the team as they journey to Tatton Old Hall. They investigate reports of a misogynistic presence as well as a mischievous spirit who plays tricks on the unwary.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Cammell Laird
programme.desc: Untimely death, fear and vast emptiness await the team in Merseyside. They investigate the offices and huge construction hall of what was once the heart of the Cammell Laird shipyard.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Sutton House
programme.desc: Musician and amateur ghost hunter Lee Ryan joins Yvette as the team encounter poltergeists, fear and phantoms at Sutton House. They find a veritable treasure trove of reported paranormal activity.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Tatton Park Mansion
programme.desc: The crew investigates Tatton Park Mansion. There is so much reported paranormal activity within its walls that certain phantoms must walk the grounds because there is no room for them inside.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Matlock Bath Pavilion
programme.desc: The team travels to the spa town of Matlock Bath to investigate strange phenomena in the pavilion. Once a tourist destination, it is now home to a mining museum, a night club and ghostly apparitions.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Hever Castle
programme.desc: The majestic location of Hever Castle in Kent is inextricably linked to the doomed relationship between King Henry VIII and Anne Boleyn. What regal phantoms will the investigation reveal?

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Basinger's New York
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark's assignment at Christmastime is to show a disillusioned columnist that there's still some good out there.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: All That Glitters
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark pose as priests in order to re-open an abandoned church as a shelter when a major fire breaks out in a neighborhood.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Wally
programme.desc: Wally is a hobo and street puppeteer whose caring and goodness have made him an angel without him knowing it.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song of Songs
programme.desc: A struggling pianist tries to start life again after a heart attack.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Night to Remember
programme.desc: High school seniors hope they get the dates they want for prom.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Mother and a Daughter
programme.desc: An estranged daughter is writing a vengeful expose about her mother, a much-beloved movie star.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Normal People
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark visit a halfway house for people who were confined to mental facilities but released because they were deemed no longer a danger to society.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: No Time For Dad
programme.desc: David is a fire captain at work and has a wife and seven kids at home. His responsibilities have taken their toll, and he feels like an old man of the firehouse. Can David's look go from lukewarm to smoldering?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Janice Holmes
programme.desc: Wife and mother, Janice Holmes,42, was used to living it large. Then she lost more than three stone in weight, and stubbed out her forty-a-day fag habit, to become a picture of health.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Kim Edgecombe
programme.desc: Fiona McDonald and the "10 Years" team of experts gear up for their toughest challenge yet! Kim Edgecombe is living proof that smoking really does cause premature aging. Kim needs help, but are the team too late?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Heather Williams Re-Visit
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones revisits 42-year-old Heather Williams from Essex.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Pageantry Days Once Again
programme.desc: Marci is a former pageant girl, but kids, stress and lack of attention to her looks have sent her appearance south. With the help of a rare triple dose of doctor treatments and a Glam Squad overhaul, Marci hopes to remove the years of neglect.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Richard Power
programme.desc: Serial socialiser and budding nightclub entrepreneur Richard Power knows he looks old for his age. But even when a poll of 100 people confirm his thoughts he has difficulty accepting it's because he's drinking 35 pints a week and 40 cigarettes a day.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Shirley Maddison
programme.desc: Shirley's lack of self confidence stems from her poor self image. She thinks she looks old. She's not the only one. A public poll guessed her age at 52. The time for serious intervention has arrived from Nicky Hambleton-Jones.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Laura Hammond
programme.desc: 34 year old Laura Hammond has a body to die for. Her stomach is flat; her slim legs go all the way up to her chin and she's got the sassy ass of a super model. According to a poll of 100 Mancunians, this young woman looks like a 48 year old!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Finding Her Hidden Value
programme.desc: Tracy is a real estate appraiser who can't seem to find the value in her looks. She works in a man's world where her clothes are usually more butch than beautiful. With a new job starting soon, Tracy needs to re-vamp her look fast.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Officer Hottie
programme.desc: Rosario is Mr. Mom by day and a New York City police officer by night. He spends his life outdoors which has done a number on his skin while his massive dental issues have done a number on his wallet. We're going to try to make him look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Different Strokes
programme.desc: Zuri is a hard working single mother of two with no time or energy for herself. In a relationship with a man her own age who looks younger, she is embarrassed to be mistaken for his mother. The Glam Squad does their magic to roll back the years.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rockin' Mom
programme.desc: Suddenly, Eva is a new wife and mother. This change in lifestyle has found her lazy and abandoning her once trendy and hip sense of style. Experts are waiting in the wings to refresh this weary mother.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Ed release two cheetah brothers together, a symbol of their new partnership, but not all of the family are happy about this new start. Caroline is still furious at what she sees as Danny's betrayal of Du Plessis.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: The family are still estranged following Caroline's decision to move back to the decrepit Clearwater house with Du Plessis. Rosie is determined to reunite everyone, and plans a civilised dinner as a step towards reconciliation.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: Strange things are happening at Leopard's Den. The family awake to find frogs everywhere, seemingly having rained down overnight; the giraffe refuses to budge from the front gate and the cheetah is off its food.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 1
programme.desc: New Year's Eve at Leopard's Den. Alice has returned, but the stress of combining work with caring for baby Bobby is causing tension between her and Danny. Liv is furious that Fatani hasn't told his mother about their relationship.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 4
programme.desc: A Glenbrook farmer has been left seriously injured after one of his Highland cows has taken to him with its horns.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: The team are being sent out to a traumatic accident that will end up being rather close to home.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: The Rescue chopper team is en route to Whitianga to help save a badly injured stock car driver.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: The chopper team are about to take off to rescue a seriously injured man.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 2
programme.desc: Fishing buddies Scott, Wayne and Wayne's son Andrew head out to their favorite fishing spot, but when a freak wave hits their boat they have no choice but to SOS for help. Within minutes, the boat capsizes. Can the Air Rescue crew get to them in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 3

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper team is responding to a life threatening emergency.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 9

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 10

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 11

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 12

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Made In: Kiekert
programme.desc: Kiekert from North Rhine-Westphalia in Germany is a supplier for many different locking systems and the market leader in side door locks. Customers from all over the world buy door locks from Kiekert.

programme.title: Made In: Audi R8 GT
programme.desc: By now, Audi has sold more than 16,000 sports cars around the world. In 2010 they upped the stakes even more and introduced the Audi R8 GT. The high performance sports car is limited on 333 units.

programme.title: Made In: Alpina
programme.desc: Alpina symbolizes modern engineering, high precision in engine design and finest materials. The green and blue cachet has guaranteed highest quality for more than 40 years. Alpina specializes in premium BMW tuning and successful motorsports.

programme.title: Made In: Self-Driving Cars
programme.desc: Autonomous driving, which means that the car operates independently, sounds like a crazy idea, but is seen as the future of mobility. Steps towards this reality are already done thanks to the progress made in Germany.

programme.title: Made In: BMW Series 5 GT, Part 1
programme.desc: In 2003 the automotive industry was booming like never before and the law of supply and the supply-demand system works perfectly. So many manufacturers decided to develop new cars.

programme.title: Made In: BMW Series 5 GT, Part 2
programme.desc: The automotive industry is a brutal business and the genesis of new models is a jealousy kept secret. However, Made In was able to document the production history of a BMW model.

programme.title: Made In: Volkner Mobile
programme.desc: With its length of up to 12 meters and its weight of 18 tons, the Performance by Volkner is the most extraordinary luxury motor home from Germany and one of the most exclusive carvans in the world.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Adventure bike for globetrotters / Bike Tour through Scotland
programme.desc: The Honda Africa Twin is back. From 1988 to 2004, it was the ultimate bike for enduro fans. The model of the modern era is hunting down the competition from BMW and KTM. We investigate the secret of its success.
programme.sub-title: Adventure bike for globetrotters / Bike Tour through Scotland

programme.title: Motorcycles: BMW
programme.desc: An incredible 215 hp with a total weight of only 149 kilos: the BMW HP4 RACE is a true racing bike. The model is limited and highly sought-after.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Carbon-Bikes / Ducati
programme.desc: Carbon has been used in racing for decades. But it's new that the lightweight yet very strong material is finding favour in motorbike construction. And it is this kind of lightweight construction that racing driver Julius Ilmberger specialises in.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Harley-Davidson
programme.desc: Dyna Switchback, Sportster 72 and Softail Slim were the names of the Harley newcomers on show in the showrooms. They appealed to completely different target groups, which each of the three motorbikes managed to do in its own unique way.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Honda / KTM / Suzuki
programme.desc: The 1970s are back. For years, motorbike nostalgia has been spreading all over the world. Honda once produced the first ever four-cylinder bike, the CB 750 Four. Now the Japanese are invoking their own tradition with the CB 1100 EX.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Mythos Tourist Trophy
programme.desc: The Tourist Trophy: since 1907, 150 racers have been racing across the Isle of Man at more than 300 km/h every year. This race has its own special charm.

programme.title: Motorcycles: Headlight Test / Schuberth Motorcycle Helmets / Zero SR
programme.desc: See and be seen. More than with other vehicles, this is vital with a motorbike. Lighting technology is particularly crucial to this. New technologies are gradually replacing the traditional incandescent lamps.
programme.sub-title: Headlight Test / Schuberth Motorcycle Helmets / Zero SR
